```java
import org.json.JSONArray;
import org.json.JSONObject;

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String javadoc = "/* Gets the current value at position {@code i}. */\n" +
                "/* @param i the index */\n" +
                "@return the current value\n" +
                "*/";

        String method = "get";
        JSONArray params = new JSONArray("[{'type': {'qualified_name': 'int', 'simple_name': 'int', 'is_array': False, 'array_dimensions': 0}, 'name': 'i'}]");
        JSONObject returnType = new JSONObject("{'qualified_name': 'double', 'simple_name': 'double', 'is_array': False, 'array_dimensions': 0}");
        String[] availableMethods = {"int length()", "double get(int i)", "double getAndAdd(int i,double delta)", "double addAndGet(int i,double delta)"};

        generateAssertions(javadoc, method, params, returnType, availableMethods);
    }

    private static void generateAssertions(String javadoc, String method, JSONArray params, JSONObject returnType, String[] availableMethods) {
        System.out.println(JSON.stringify({
            "description": "the index must be an integer",
            "assertion": `assert ${args[0].get("qualified_name")} instanceof ${returnType.get("qualified_name")};`,
            "name": "i",
            "content": "the index"
        }));

        for (String availableMethod : availableMethods) {
            if (availableMethod.contains(method)) {
                int startIndex = availableMethod.indexOf("(");
                int endIndex = availableMethod.lastIndexOf(")");
                String methodParamName = availableMethod.substring(startIndex + 1, endIndex).split(",")[0].trim();
                System.out.println(JSON.stringify({
                    "description": `the ${method} must be called with a valid index`,
                    "assertion": `assert ${args[0].get("qualified_name")} == ${returnType.get("qualified_name")}(args[${methodParamName.split("=").indexOf("i").length * -1 + 1}]));`,
                    "name": method,
                    "content": `the ${method}`
                }));
            }
        }
    }

}
```

This Java code takes the provided Javadoc, method name, parameters, return type, and available instance methods as inputs. It generates pre-condition assertions based on the given information and prints them to the console.

Note that this code assumes that the `args` array is passed as a parameter to the method. Also, it uses the `JSON.stringify()` function from the JSON library to format the output in the required format.

Please note that you need to include the necessary dependencies (JSON library) while compiling and running this Java code.
